15 WHEREAS, his significant organizational and leadership talents, his remarkable patience
16 and diplomacy, his keen sense of vision, and his sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of this
17 state have earned him the respect and admiration of his colleagues and associates; and
18 WHEREAS, Mr. Hudgins's leadership has been invaluable to numerous organizations,
19 including the Board of Managers for the Association County Commissioners of Georgia and
20 the Albany-Dougherty Economic Development Commission; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable and distinguished
22 Georgian be recognized appropriately by dedicating an intersection in his honor.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
24 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the intersection of State Route 234/Gillionville Road and
25 Eight Mile Road in Dougherty County is dedicated as the Lamar Hudgins Intersection.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
27 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Lamar Hudgins Intersection.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Mr.
30 Lamar Hudgins and to the Department of Transportation.
